Hey Rich, 
Gene called me this morning about more bad findings on the Barge. Items Boscoe didn't mention before the 
Barge went down... 
-Fabrication of Splash guards for gate: Because it doesn't have a splash guard everything gets wet on the barge 
during transport. pies 1-8 
-Need to install 6 new Zincs underneath Big N: Existing Zincs are bad and worn out which is bad because it 
protects the engines and all components. see pies 9-14 
-Power wash inside & Paint: Need sandblasting and paint job in the inside as well. see pics 21-28 
-Seals worn out in steering shaft and Engine hatch: The Steering shaft seals are worn out. see pies (15-18) the 
seals and screws for the Engine hatch weren't put back together properly so water was going into the engine 
room. see pics 24-25 
-Repair cracks on barge gate and barge: The gate is cracking off from the barge. see pies 29-30 
Note: Awaiting quote from Island Rigging and Hydraulics for the leaking Hydraulic filters in the engine room 
